❌ TEMPLATE LITERALS DO NOT WORK
   • Filter still checks characters inside template literals
   • No special processing bypasses the character filter

✅ SPECIAL CHARACTERS ARE ALLOWED
   • Characters that passed: " (quote), ; (semicolon), / (slash)
   • Can escape string context and comment out code
   • BUT: Need to construct meaningful JavaScript without alphanumerics

⚠️  APPLICATION HAS TWO LAYERS OF VALIDATION:
   1. Character filter (blocks a-z, A-Z, 0-9)
   2. Runtime validation (checks if code executes properly)

